manifest.name: GitSense Chat CLI Provenance & Governance Brain
manifest.description: Governance layer for AI-generated code in gsc-cli, ensuring traceability, metadata integrity, and AI-readiness. This manifest validates that code block headers remain accurate (Metadata Integrity) and assesses whether code documentation provides sufficient context for AI agents (Code Documentation Quality). It enables "Smarter and Safer" development by identifying governance risks and ensuring the repository remains auditable.

analyzers.name: GSC Provenance Integrity Auditor - Metadata-Validation
analyzers.description: Validates the honesty and accuracy of AI-generated code metadata, ensuring traceability headers remain truthful as code evolves.

analyzers.name: GSC-CLI Code Documentation Quality Analyzer
analyzers.description: Evaluates the quality, honesty, and completeness of code documentation to determine AI-readiness and maintenance burden.

fields.name: layer
fields.description: The architectural layer of the file (e.g., cli, internal-logic, data-access, pkg-util, config).

fields.name: traceability_status
fields.description: The completeness of the traceability header (Full, Partial, None).

fields.name: description_accuracy
fields.description: The accuracy of the Description field (Accurate, Stale, Missing).

fields.name: governance_risk
fields.description: The assessed risk level (None, Low, Medium, High).

fields.name: risk_factors
fields.description: A list of specific issues identified during analysis.

fields.name: recommendations
fields.description: A list of actions needed to improve governance.

fields.name: documentation_quality
fields.description: The overall assessment of the volume and depth of comments and docstrings. Allowed values: "Comprehensive", "Adequate", "Minimal".

fields.name: intent_clarity
fields.description: The degree to which the code explains "why" it exists versus just "what" it does. Allowed values: "High", "Medium", "Low".

fields.name: ai_readiness_score
fields.description: A functional score (0-100) representing how safely an AI agent could refactor this file without human supervision.

fields.name: missing_context
fields.description: A list of specific areas where context is lacking (e.g., "error-handling", "side-effects").

fields.name: maintenance_burden
fields.description: An assessment of how much "tribal knowledge" is required to maintain the code. Allowed values: "Low", "Medium", "High".

fields.name: analysis_rationale
fields.description: A concise explanation (2-3 sentences) of the key evidence that drove the scoring.
